Threat Intelligence Check (Python Script)

python
import requests

API_KEY = "***YOUR_API_KEY***"
OTX_URL = "https://otx.alienvault.com/api/v1/indicators/domain/{}/general"

def check_domain_threat(domain):
    url = OTX_URL.format(domain)
    headers = {"X-OTX-API-KEY": API_KEY}
    response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    if response.status_code == 200:
        data = response.json()
        pulses = data.get("pulse_info", {}).get("count", 0)
        print(f"[INFO] Threat Intel hits for {domain}: {pulses}")
    else:
        print("[ERROR] Failed to fetch intel")

check_domain_threat("example.com")

Exploitation Simulation

    Example: SQL Injection test using SQLMap

    bash
    sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page.php?id=1" --batch --dump

Report Generation (Python Template)

python
import pandas as pd

findings = [
    {"Vulnerability": "SQL Injection", "Severity": "High", "Fix": "Use parameterized queries"},
    {"Vulnerability": "Outdated Apache Server", "Severity": "Medium", "Fix": "Upgrade to latest version"},
]

df = pd.DataFrame(findings)
df.to_html("Security_Report.html")
print("Report generated: Security_Report.html")
